## Performance

**~100-500× SLOWER** than double (possibly even slower depending on implementation):

```aria
// Benchmark estimate: 1M operations
// double:  ~2ms
// flt128:  ~100-200ms
// flt256:  ~200-1000ms (or worse!)

// Every arithmetic operation is emulated in software
// No hardware support exists anywhere
flt256:sum = 0.0f256;
for (tbb32:i = 0i32; i < 1000000i32; ++i) {
    sum += flt256(i);  // VERY SLOW
}
```

**Memory**: 32 bytes per value (4× double, 2× flt128, 8× float)

**Cache**: Holds 1/4 as many values as double (severe cache pressure)

