## Limb-Based Implementation (LBIM Extended)

### Internal Structure

```c
// From include/runtime/lbim_extended.h

#define ARIA_INT4096_LIMBS 64

typedef struct {
    uint64_t limbs[64];  // 64 × 64-bit = 4096 bits = 512 bytes
} aria_int4096_t;

// ⚠️ MEMORY NOTE: Each int4096 value is HALF A KILOBYTE!
// Use sparingly. Consider int2048 or int1024 if possible.
```

### Performance Implications

**Stack allocation**:
```aria
// This allocates 512 bytes on the stack!
int4096:value = 0i4096;

// 10 × int4096 = 5 KB of stack
int4096:array[10];  // (future array syntax)

// For large arrays, heap allocation preferred
```

**Cache behavior**:
- Modern L1 cache line: 64 bytes
- One int4096 value: 512 bytes = **8 cache lines**
- Operations may thrash cache if many values active

