# int1024 - 1024-bit Integer (RSA-4096)

**Category**: Types → Large Integers / Cryptography  
**Purpose**: Post-quantum cryptography, RSA-4096 key operations  
**Status**: ⚠️ PARTIAL IMPLEMENTATION (Basic ops complete, division in progress)

---

## Overview

**int1024** is a **1024-bit signed integer** type designed for post-quantum cryptographic operations, particularly RSA-4096 which requires 4096-bit modular arithmetic (two 1024-bit primes  multiplied).

---

## Key Characteristics

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| **Total Bits** | 1024 (16 × 64-bit limbs) |
| **Range (signed)** | -2^1023 to +2^1023 - 1 |
| **Range (unsigned)** | 0 to 2^1024 - 1 |
| **Storage** | 128 bytes (16 limbs) |
| **ERR Sentinel** | limbs[15]=0x8000000000000000, others=0 |
| **Endianness** | Little-endian limbs |

---

## Representation

### Memory Layout

```aria
int1024 = {
    uint64:limbs[16];  // Little-endian: limbs[0] = LSB, limbs[15] = MSB
};

// Total: 128 bytes
// Limb 0: bits 0-63
// Limb 1: bits 64-127
// ...
// Limb 15: bits 960-1023 (sign bit in bit 1023)
```

### LLVM IR Type

```llvm
%struct.int1024 = type { [16 x i64] }
```

---

## Declaration

```aria
// Basic declaration
int1024:rsa_modulus;
uint1024:large_number;

// Initialization (future - literal syntax)
int1024:value = 123456789012345678901234567890i1024;

// From hex (future)
int1024:hex_val = 0x123456789ABCDEF...i1024;
```

---

## Arithmetic Operations

### Addition & Subtraction

```aria
int1024:a = ...;  // Large number
int1024:b = ...;  // Large number

int1024:sum = a + b;      // Multi-precision addition with carry
int1024:diff = a - b;     // Multi-precision subtraction with borrow

// Overflow detection (returns ERR)
int1024:max = MAX_INT1024;
int1024:overflow = max + max;  // Returns ERR sentinel
```

### Multiplication

```aria
int1024:a = ...;
int1024:b = ...;

int1024:product = a * b;  // 2048-bit intermediate, truncates to 1024-bit

// For cryptography, often need full 2048-bit result
// (future: widening multiply returning int2048)
```

### Division & Modulo (In Progress)

```aria
int1024:dividend = ...;
int1024:divisor = ...;

// Unsigned division
int1024:quotient = aria_lbim_udiv1024(dividend, divisor);
int1024:remainder = aria_lbim_umod1024(dividend, divisor);

// Signed division  
int1024:s_quotient = aria_lbim_sdiv1024(dividend, divisor);
int1024:s_remainder = aria_lbim_smod1024(dividend, divisor);

// Division by zero returns ERR (not crash)
int1024:zero = 0i1024;
int1024:bad = dividend / zero;  // ERR sentinel
```

---

## ERR Sentinel Pattern

### ERR Value

```aria
// ERR = minimum signed value (1 << 1023)
// Limbs: [0, 0, 0, ..., 0, 0x8000000000000000]

int1024:err = ERR;  // ERR sentinel

// Same pattern as fix256, int1024 family
// Cannot be produced by valid arithmetic (reserved)
```

### ERR Propagation

```aria
int1024:bad = ERR;
int1024:good = 100i1024;

int1024:still_err = bad + good;      // ERR (sticky!)
int1024:also_err = good * bad;       // ERR
int1024:div_err = good / bad;        // ERR

// Errors propagate automatically
if (result == ERR) {
    stderr.write("Cryptographic operation failed!\n");
    !!! ERR_CRYPTO_FAILURE;
}
```

---

## Cryptographic Operations

### RSA-4096 Key Generation (Conceptual)

```aria
// RSA-4096 uses two 2048-bit primes
// Each 2048-bit prime requires int1024 arithmetic

int1024:p = generate_large_prime_1024();  // First prime
int1024:q = generate_large_prime_1024();  // Second prime

// In actual RSA-4096, these would be int2048 primes
// But intermediate operations use int1024 limb arithmetic

if (p == ERR || q == ERR) {
    stderr.write("Prime generation failed\n");
    !!! ERR_CRYPTO_KEYGEN;
}
```

### Modular Arithmetic

```aria
// Modular exponentiation (foundation of RSA)
// base^exponent mod modulus

int1024:base = ...;
int1024:exponent = ...;
int1024:modulus = ...;

int1024:result = mod_exp_1024(base, exponent, modulus);

// Used in RSA signature verification:
// signature^e mod n == hash(message)
```

### GCD (Greatest Common Divisor)

```aria
// Euclidean algorithm for GCD
int1024:a = ...;
int1024:b = ...;

function gcd_1024(int1024:a, int1024:b) : int1024 begin
    till b == 0i1024 loop
        int1024:temp = b;
        b = a % b;  // Modulo operation
        a = temp;

        if (b == ERR) {
            return ERR;
        }
    end
    return a;
end

// Used to verify e and phi(n) are coprime in RSA
```

---

## Bitwise Operations

```aria
int1024:a = ...;
int1024:b = ...;

// Logical operations (all 1024 bits)
int1024:and_result = a & b;
int1024:or_result = a | b;
int1024:xor_result = a ^ b;
int1024:not_result = ~a;

// Shifts (multi-limb cascading)
int1024:left = a << 10;   // Left shift 10 bits
int1024:right = a >> 10;  // Arithmetic right shift (sign-extended)

// Used in cryptographic mixing functions
```

---

## Comparison Operations

```aria
int1024:a = ...;
int1024:b = ...;

// Comparison (multi-limb, MSB first)
bool:equal = (a == b);
bool:not_equal = (a != b);
bool:less = (a < b);
bool:greater = (a > b);
bool:less_equal = (a <= b);
bool:greater_equal = (a >= b);

// ERR comparisons
if (a == ERR || b == ERR) {
    // ERR detected, abort comparison
}
```

